# Membership Website Page Content Directions

This document outlines the structure, content requirements, and layout guidance for the membership-related pages of the website. These directions are intended to guide designers, developers, and content creators in building the membership section of the platform.

# 1\. Membership Landing Page

## Page Purpose

The membership landing page introduces the overall membership offering and helps prospective members understand the value of the platform. Its primary goal is to convert visitors into members by guiding them toward selecting a plan.

## Page Layout

### 1\. Hero Section

Purpose: Immediately communicate the core value of the membership.

Content: - Headline explaining the platform value - Short supporting description - Call-to-action button (View Plans / Join Now) - Optional supporting visual or product screenshot

Example elements: - Headline - Subheadline - Primary CTA - Secondary CTA (Explore Features)

### 2\. Membership Overview

Purpose: Introduce the platform pillars.

Display the core components of the membership: - DocShare - Partner Marketplace - Knowledge Center - Advisory Services - Support

Each component should include: - Icon or visual - Short description - Link to learn more

### 3\. How the Membership Works

Purpose: Explain the platform experience.

Suggested format: Three-step visual explanation.

Step 1 - Explore resources Step 2 - Implement systems Step 3 - Improve and scale the business

### 4\. Key Platform Features

Purpose: Highlight the strongest features.

Examples: - AI Document Generator - Business Systems Library (DocShare) - Partner Marketplace - Business Advisory Access - Implementation Support

Use feature cards or icons.

### 5\. Membership Plan Comparison

Purpose: Help users compare plans.

Include a simplified pricing table showing: - Basic - Lifetime - Standard - Premium

Show only key differences.

Include CTA buttons under each plan.

### 6\. Example Use Cases

Purpose: Show how businesses use the platform.

Example sections: - Improve operational processes - Implement documentation systems - Generate business policies - Access expert advisory

### 7\. Testimonials or Social Proof

Purpose: Increase trust.

Examples: - member testimonials - client success stories - business outcomes

### 8\. FAQ Section

Purpose: Answer common questions.

Pull questions from the FAQ document.

### 9\. Final Call to Action

Purpose: Encourage sign-up.

Elements: - Headline - Summary of value - CTA button (Choose Your Plan)

